title: For Sale:  SOLD: Steyr Austrian Made Mod. 1912 Mauser in 7.62x51
postcontent: SOLD: This is a Steyr Mauser Model 1912 made in Austria. As you can see, the rifle is in excellent condition. I had the bolt handle professionally forged and polished for scope usage by Fincer's- a Gunsmith that specializes in bolt work in Texas. That was a $75 service and well worth it. I also invested in the historically correct reproduction sling which cost $50. This sling was custom made by Welser Militaria In AMERICA and is not to be confused with those that come from China. This sling has new old stock original equipment hardware which is much better in quality than the Chinese made slings out there for $20. This sling has an authentic NOS quick disconnect rear swivel so that you can mount it either to the buttstock or the "parade" mount at the trigger guard. The Steyr Mauser is one of the finest Mausers made in terms of quality, fit and finish.This is a re-arsenaled rifle that was, from my understanding, done sometime in the 1950s and at that time they rebarreled the rifle with a modern 7.62x51 NATO chambered barrel. It is one of the finest examples I have seen of these special Mausers. It definitely has not seen much use since the re-arsenal and the barrel is in near new condition with strong and shiny rifling. Because it is chambered in the all-around and plentiful 7.62 NATO/ .308 round, it is the perfect "shooter" Mauser. I have this listed at a flat out bargain considering the condition, the rarity, the newly forged and polished bolt, the Austrian Steyr quality and the new historically correct sling. This a rare rifle, not a "moonrock" as Larry Vickers would say, but definately hard to get your hands on. I have it priced to move quickly to the astute buyer. For better and many more prictures I have this simultaneously listed on Gunbroker:  http://www.gunbroker.com/item/618114351  I am not interested in any trades and my price is absolutely firm.
